# NOTE on hostname canonicalization: `_redirects` only accepts relative
# paths on the LHS. Cloudflare Redirect Rules can't match `*.pages.dev`
# either (that traffic flows through the pages.dev zone, which we don't
# control). So pages.dev → apex relies on the `<link rel="canonical">`
# tag emitted by Seo.astro — Google honors that as a consolidation
# signal. See docs/deployment.md for the full reasoning and the
# fallback (a Pages middleware) if direct hits become a problem.

# Common sitemap aliases → the actual sitemap index
/sitemap.xml      /sitemap-index.xml  301
/sitemap_index.xml /sitemap-index.xml  301
/sitemap          /sitemap-index.xml  301

# Common feed aliases → the canonical RSS feed
/feed             /rss.xml            301
/feed.xml         /rss.xml            301
/atom.xml         /rss.xml            301
